We enjoin upon you moreover, beloved son the prior, in virtue of obedience and under pain of excommunication, which not without desert you shall be able to fear, if you do not that which we command, that, if any quarrels, bickerin gs, strifes or disagreements arise henceforth among the brethren of the same monastery, you fail not to inform and notify us as soon as you may, without the evasion of any delay, touching the same and their instigators and accomplices.

Given under our scal, etc., [in our manor] of Nettleham, on the first day of April in the year of our Lord 1440, and the thirteenth year of our consecration and fourth of our translation.
